        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "chore: harden npm shrinkwrap release path",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Ship the root OpenClaw npm package and every OpenClaw-owned publishable npm plugin with generated `npm-shrinkwrap.json` files.\n- Generate shrinkwrap from the published npm dependency graph, strip dev deps, and apply `pnpm-workspace.yaml` override policy.\n- Add shrinkwrap and `package-lock.json` to the dependency security review surface through CODEOWNERS, dependency-change awareness, labeler sizing, and dependency report output.\n- Enforce root shrinkwrap in release/package validators, check plugin-local shrinkwrap before plugin pack/publish, and document the root/plugin contract.\n\n## Explainer\n`npm-shrinkwrap.json` is npm's publishable lockfile. Unlike `package-lock.json`, npm can include it in published packages, so installing `openclaw` or an OpenClaw-owned npm plugin can resolve through the reviewed dependency graph that release tooling generated.\n\nThis does not replace `pnpm-lock.yaml` for source development. The repo still uses pnpm as the source-of-truth package manager. The generator derives npm shrinkwrap from each package's stock published dependency graph: root `openclaw` for the CLI/Gateway package, and `extensions/<id>/package.json` for each `publishToNpm` plugin package.\n\nPlugin installs already run through npm's managed root, so third-party packages that ship shrinkwrap are supported by npm normally. This PR makes the OpenClaw-owned plugin packages ship that lockfile too, and keeps plugin-only dependency graphs plugin-local instead of pretending the root package shrinkwrap covers them.\n\nBecause lockfiles can redirect resolved package versions and tarballs, this PR treats `pnpm-lock.yaml`, `npm-shrinkwrap.json`, and `package-lock.json` diffs as security-review surfaces. The package path rejects accidental `package-lock.json`, requires shrinkwrap for new root tarballs, and checks generated shrinkwraps have no dev dependency graph.\n\n## Verification\n- `pnpm deps:shrinkwrap:generate`\n- `pnpm deps:shrinkwrap:check`\n- `bash scripts/plugin-npm-publish.sh --pack-dry-run extensions/amazon-bedrock | jq -r '.[0].files[].path' | grep '^npm-shrinkwrap.json$'`\n- `NPM_CONFIG_CACHE=/tmp/openclaw-npm-cache npm pack --dry-run --ignore-scripts --json`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs test/scripts/dependency-change-awareness-workflow.test.ts test/scripts/dependency-changes-report.test.ts test/scripts/check-openclaw-package-tarball.test.ts test/openclaw-npm-release-check.test.ts test/package-scripts.test.ts test/package-manager-config.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs test/package-manager-config.test.ts test/plugin-npm-package-manifest.test.ts test/scripts/dependency-change-awareness-workflow.test.ts test/scripts/dependency-changes-report.test.ts test/package-scripts.test.ts`\n- `pnpm check:docs`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `actionlint .github/workflows/dependency-change-awareness.yml .github/workflows/labeler.yml`\n- `npm pack openclaw@2026.4.25 --json --pack-destination <tmp> && node scripts/check-openclaw-package-tarball.mjs <tmp>/*.tgz`\n\n## Real behavior proof\nBehavior addressed: OpenClaw root npm installs and OpenClaw-owned npm plugin installs now carry publishable shrinkwrap files, while lockfile/shrinkwrap changes are treated as security-review surfaces.\n\nReal environment tested: Local macOS checkout with root dry-run npm pack, package-local plugin pack dry-run, all generated shrinkwraps, focused Vitest coverage, docs checks, workflow linting, and a real published `openclaw@2026.4.25` tarball compatibility check.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Generated and checked root plus 30 plugin shrinkwraps, verified `extensions/amazon-bedrock` pack dry-run includes `npm-shrinkwrap.json`, ran focused tests for release/tarball/dependency-review/plugin-package surfaces, docs check, actionlint, and legacy published tarball validation.\n\nEvidence after fix: Root dry-run pack includes `npm-shrinkwrap.json` and excludes `package-lock.json`; generated plugin shrinkwraps exist for all 30 `publishToNpm` plugin packages; plugin shrinkwrap checks report current; selected generated shrinkwraps have 0 dev packages; Bedrock plugin pack dry-run emits `npm-shrinkwrap.json` in the packed file list.\n\nObserved result after fix: Release/package checks and focused tests pass; the legacy published tarball emits a legacy shrinkwrap warning and passes; docs check passes; workflow lint and diff checks pass.\n\nWhat was not tested: Full release CI, broad `pnpm check`, and an actual npm/plugin publish.\n",
